  "prompt": "Septoplasty at fortis?",
  "response": "Fortis Healthcare is a well-known chain of hospitals in India, offering a variety of medical services, including ENT (Ear, Nose, and Throat) procedures such as septoplasty. Septoplasty is a surgical procedure used to correct a deviated septum, which can lead to breathing difficulties and other issues.\n\nIf you're considering a septoplasty at Fortis or any other hospital, here are a few things you might want to consider:\n\n1. **Consultation**: Schedule a consultation with an ENT specialist to evaluate your condition and determine if septoplasty is necessary for you.\n\n2. **Procedure Details**: Ask about the procedure, recovery time, and any potential risks or complications.\n\n3. **Cost**: Inquire about the cost of the procedure, including any additional fees for consultations, anesthesia, and hospital stay.\n\n4. **Facilities**: Fortis hospitals are known for their advanced medical facilities and experienced medical staff, which can be reassuring.\n\n5. **Insurance**: Check if your health insurance covers the procedure and what documentation might be required.\n\n6. **Follow-Up Care**: Understand the post-operative care process and any follow-up appointments that will be necessary.\n\nFor specific details, it's best to contact Fortis Healthcare directly or visit their official website for more information.",
